result.execSummary:
Jon K Gasner was found not guilty on all charges in this case. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jon K Gasner is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

St. vs Gasner
8:15am Court calls case and appearances. Court speaks re: Jury Instructions. Video and photo graphs
will not be allowed into the trial. Court speaks to the parties. State speaks to the court. Atty Amann
speaks to the court. Court speaks findings re: motion on prior convictions. Nothing further from the
state. Atty Amann speaks to the court. Off record at 8:35am
9:00am 20 jurors seated. Court calls case and appearances. Clerk swears in Jury members. Court
reviews complaint to the jury panel. Court begins questioning jury panel. Juror 172 excused. Court
continues questioning. Off record for private questioning. Juror questioned out of public area. Back on
record at 9:44am. Off record for private discussion/break. Back on record at 10:09am. No additional
questions from the court. Nothing from the state. Atty Amann questions the jury panel. Attorneys
strike jurors. Court calls selected Jurors. Clerk swears in jury panel. Off record at 10:28.
Back on record at 10:38am Jury returns. Court begins reading jury instructions. State gives opening
statement. Atty Amann gives opening statement. State calls Kristina Moe to the stand. Clerk swears in
Ms. Moe. State begins questioning. Atty Amann objects. Jury steps down. Atty Amann makes objection.
State speaks to the court. Atty Amann questions the witness. State speaks to the court. Court speaks to
the parties. Jury returns. State continues questioning. State offers exhibit 1-received. Court speaks to
the Jury. Off record at 12:05pm.
1:00pm on record in chambers w/ parties. Court speaks re: juror speaking to witness. Juror is
questioned, witness is questioned. Atty Amann makes a motion for a mistrial. Court denies motion. Off
record.
1:15pm back on record in court room. State speaks to the court. Atty Amann speaks to the court.
Court makes ruling re: states motion. Off record at 1:24pm. Back on record at 1:30pm. State continues
questioning Ms. Moe. State offers exhibit 2- received. State offers exhibit 3-received. State offers
exhibit 4-received. State continues questioning. Nothing further from the state. Cross from Atty
Amann. Nothing futher. Redirect from the state. Objection from Atty Amann re: exhibit Jury steps
down. Off record at 2:30pm. Back on record at 2:41pm. Nothing further from the state. Recross from
Atty Amann. Nothing further. Redirect from the state. Nothing further. Witness is excused. State calls
Deputy Brian Jilek to the stand. Clerk swears in Deputy Jilek. State begins questioning. Nothing further
from the state. Cross from Atty Amann. Nothing further-redirect from the State. Nothing further
witness excused. State rests. Jury stands down. Court speaks to parties. Court speaks to the def. re:
testifying. Court finds the def. freely and knowingly waives his right to remain silent. Off record at
3:13pm. Back on record at 3:18pm. Atty Amann calls John Gasner to the stand. Clerk swears in Mr.
Gasner. Atty Amann begins questioning. Nothing further from Atty Amann. Cross from the State. 
Nothing futher. Redirect from Atty Amann. Nothing further. Recross from the State. Nothing further,
witness is excused. Defense rests. Jury stands down. State speaks to the court. State re-calls Kristina
Moe to the stand. State begins questioning. Nothing further. Witness excused. Evidence is closed. Jury
stands down. Court reviews jury instructions w/ parties. EX21 offered, no obj. Admitted. EX Photos 2a,
3a, 4a  admitted. EX20 is not received. EX 5 is not received.
Jurors are seated, gives jury instructions. 4:51 p.m. DA Winton gives closing argument. 4:56 p.m.
Attorney Amman gives closing argument. 5:01 p.m. Rebuttal by DA Winton. 5:04 Obj by Amman. Jury
stands down. Argument by Amman. Court addresses DA Winton. Amman makes Motion for Mistrial.
Court to take motion under advisement, makes statement. 5:07 Jury is seated. 5:09 Court addresses the
juror. No further rebuttal by DA Winton. Court gives final jury instructions. 5:11 Jury stands down for
deliberations. 5:56 Jury notifies Bailiff that they have a verdict. 5:59 p.m. Court reads verdict  NG on
Count 1. Court pools the jury, unanimous. Court reads verdict Count 2  NG. Court pools the jury,
unanimous. Court receives Verdict. Court addresses the Juror, thanks them for their service. 6:01 p.m.
Jury is excused. Court addresses parties. Case is dismissed, bail to be returned to defendant.

Defendant, Jon K Gasner appeared with Attorney T. Gregory Amann.  Attorney Angeline E Winton appeared for the State.

1:03 p.m. Court recites case and appearances. Court questions counsel re: jury trial a go. Jury trial is a go. Attorney Winton makes statement re: objection to adding new discovery as there is no amended scheduling order. Attorney Amann makes argument re: does not fall into the discovery demand. Attorney Winton rebuttals re: view video prior to trial as there will be objections as it is testimonial. Court questions Attorney Winton re: demand for all video and photos. Attorney Winton makes statement that they demanded everything that will be entered in the trial. Court questions Attorney Amann re: hear DE in the background in video. Attorney Amann makes statement re: will have on mute. Attorney Amann describes what the video entails. Attorney Winton makes argument to testimonial and staging. Attorney Winton makes statement re: cannot have victim review video to clarify that it is true and accurate. Court defers ruling on video being admissable until Court and victim can review the video. Attorney Amann makes argument.  Court takes motion under advisement. Attorney Winton objects to jury instructions being filed 04-12-2017 as they should have been submitted after the date on the scheduling order. Attorney Amann makes argument. Attorney Winton rebuttals. Attorney Amann makes agrument re: one instruction. If the evidence supports the instruction, the Court is ordered to include it by law. Court allows the jury instruction to be added. Attorney Winton makes statement re: motion in limine re: prior convictions. Court reviews motion. Attorney Winton makes argument to include the convictions as impeachment purposes.  Attorney Amann makes argument re: to not include as he does not agree with them. Attorney Winton marks Exhibits 1-3. Court questions Attorney Amann re: counsel in most recent case. Attorney Amann makes statement re: no counsel. Court questions Attorney Winton if that changes things. Attorney Winton makes agrument. Nothing further from the State. Court will take the motion in limine under advisement. Attorney Winton provides the Court with her copy of the CD with video and pictures. Parties are to appear by 8 o'clock day of trial to go over decisions.
